article.headline: (21) DEPAUL 70, NORTHERN ILLINOIS 60
article.story:
DEKALB, Illinois (Ticker) -- Khara Smith recorded a 
double-double and Jenni Dant scored 20 points to help No. 21
DePaul beat Northern Illinois, 70-60.

Smith, a sophomore forward, recorded her ninth double-double of
the year with 24 points on 8-of-14 shooting and 12 rebounds. She
also collected five steals for the Blue Demons, who jumped out
to a 19-0 lead early in the first half and took 24 more
free-throw attempts than the Huskies.

Dant shot a perfect 12-for-12 from the free-throw line for
DePaul (12-1), which tied the best-ever start in school history.

Charlene Smith and Ashley Luke both chipped in with 13 points
for the Blue Demons, who entered the contest averaging 93.8
points per game, but shot just 34 percent from the floor.

Joi Scott scored 17 points off the bench and Stephanie Raymond
netted nine points and grabbed 10 rebound, but committed seven
of the 25 turnovers for Northern Illinois (5-6).

Lindsey Secrest added 11 points for the Huskies, who fell to
7-25 all-time against DePaul despite outscoring the Blue Demon's
bench by a 24-0 margin.
